-- Canary Wharf Group shareholder Franklin backs Songbird deal-bidders 
-- By Carolyn Cohn
-- Tue Dec 30, 2014 02:28AM EST
-- None



LONDON, Dec 30 (Reuters) - Franklin Mutual Advisers has written to Songbird Estates <SBDE.L> to indicate it plans to accept any cash offer for Canary Wharf Group shares from a Qatari-led group bidding for Songbird.

News of the letter was given as the bidders for Songbird, Qatar Investment Authority (QIA) and its bidding partner, U.S. investor Brookfield Property Partners <BPY.N>, published the final offer document for their 2.6 billion pound ($4 billiion) bid for Songbird.